{{Italic title}}
'''''Ibsen Studies''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering research on the [[playwright]] [[Henrik Ibsen]]. It is published biannually by [[Routledge]] in cooperation with the [[Centre for Ibsen Studies]] ([[University of Oslo]]). It was originally published under the title ''Ibsenårbok'' (Ibsen's Annual) by [[Universitetsforlaget]] from 1952 to 1988. From 1988 to 2000, it was published by Universitetsforlaget as ''Contemporary approaches to Ibsen''.

The journal is classified as a level 2 journal, meaning the journal is considered leading in the field of [[literature]] studies, in the [[Norwegian Scientific Index]], published by the [[Ministry of Education and Research (Norway)|Ministry of Education and Research]].<ref>[http://dbh.nsd.uib.no/kanaler/kanalDetalj.do?produktid=441309&bibsys= Norwegian Social Science Data Services – Scientific journals, series and publishers]</ref>

