{{Infobox journal | title = Perspecta: The Yale Architectural Journal | cover = Perspecta 47 cover.jpg | caption= Front cover of issue 47 (2014) of Perspecta: The Yale Architectural Journal | editor = | discipline = [[Architecture]] | language = English | abbreviation = Perspecta | publisher = [[MIT Press]] for the [[Yale School of Architecture]] | country = US | frequency = Annually | history = 1952-present | openaccess = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://architecture.yale.edu/school/publications/perspecta | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | RSS = | atom = | JSTOR = 00790958 | OCLC = 62483181 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0079-0958 | eISSN = }} '''''Perspecta: The Yale Architectural Journal''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published since 1952 by the [[Yale School of Architecture]] and distributed by the [[MIT Press]]. Graduate students are competitively chosen to edit each issue. It is the oldest architectural journal of its kind in the United States<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.architecture.yale.edu/drupal/publications/perspecta|title=Home|website=Yale Architecture}}</ref> and is rated as an A* journal on the [[Excellence in Research for Australia]] journal list. Contributors include some of the most important figures in contemporary architecture worldwide.
