'''''Petits Propos Culinaires''''' is a journal of the [[Food history|history of food and cookery]]. Founded by [[Alan Davidson (food writer)|Alan Davidson]] in 1979, it is now edited by [[Tom Jaine]] and is published by Prospect Books. The frequency of publication, three times a year, has not varied; nor has the format. Many of the articles and notes in ''Petits Propos Culinaires'' also served to enrich the ''[[Oxford Companion to Food]]''.

